  ✒ Description:
      The Markdown mark — the familiar rounded frame enclosing an "M" and a down
      arrow — shown on the Export screen's Markdown option card. The frame is a
      stroke so it matches the weight of the Material outlined icons beside it, while
      the M and arrow are solid so they stay legible at 24dp.

  ✒ Key Features:
      - 24dp on a 24-unit viewport, matching the platform icon metric.
      - Stroked frame at 1.8 units with solid glyphs inside, for legibility at icon size.
      - Pure white: the icon is tinted by the composable that draws it.

  ✒ Other Important Information:
      Referenced from ui/ArchiveScreen.kt. XML forbids double-hyphen sequences inside
      comments and AAPT2 hard-fails on them, so this header closes with a box-drawing rule.
